three cuts from the same displaying bird, the first two natural, the last after playback.  The first cut is a shorter snippet (from further away) of song during a prolong flight display from a bird over a rocky hilltop. While giving the display the bird was flying in a large circle high up in the air with shallow, fluttery wingbeats.  The second cut comprises the entire flight display bout, from take-off to landing. The wingbeats of the bird can be heard at various points during the cut as it comes closer to the mic.  The final cut is of calls from the ground.
Equipment Notes: Telinga Pro 7 set on mono mode.

Recordist Note: "Second cut: Song from ground, took off at 0:33, chase calls start 0:39, whining male interaction calls start 0:47. habitat granitic alpine ridge."

LNS: 125 Hz AUHipass filter applied in soundBlade to the final segment.

NOTES: Long complete song in flight display with other snippets of song.  This cut is full of handling noise.  Recorded in response to repeated playbacks of its own song on tundra in the foothills of the Kigluaik Mountains on the Seward Peninsula.   In response to the playback the bird came in from over 100m and gave this flight display over our heads.  Recorded simultaneously by Gerrit Vyn.  Sound Devices 744T with 160Hz HPF, Telinga Pro6 in flat.  I've filtered this entire cut in the studio using the ZSYS z-Q2 stereo digital mastering equalizer at S-95.0 500Hz. Other Behaviors: Flush, Advertise. Habitat: Tundra, Arctic Tundra.
